<paragraph id="8B933F46FFEBFF9CFCFEF9091E18FF44" blockId="4.[136,1452,979,2085]" lastBlockId="5.[136,1451,158,221]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="69" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DFCFEF9091BE0F925" box="[189,253,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">Notes</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEBFF9DFD62F909192CF925" authorityName="Y. Feng, S. N. Zhang &amp; Z. Y. Liu" authorityYear="2022" box="[289,561,1699,1725]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bambucicola">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DFD62F909192CF925" box="[289,561,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">Fissuroma bambucicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
morphologically lines well with 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEBFF9DFFE9F9091F3CF925" box="[938,1057,1700,1725]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DFFE9F9091F3CF925" box="[938,1057,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">Fissuroma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having carbonaceous ascomata with slit-like ostioles and fusiform, hyaline ascospores. Multi-gene phylogenetic analyses showed that it has a close relationship with 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEBFF9DFDDBF9411920F89D" box="[408,573,1772,1797]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aggregatum">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DFDDBF9411920F89D" box="[408,573,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">F. aggregatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode id="ED3DA783FFEBFF9DFE13F946196BF89D" box="[592,630,1771,1797]" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">KT</collectionCode>
984). However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEBFF9DFF7DF9411F5BF89D" box="[830,1094,1772,1797]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aggregatum">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DFF7DF9411F5BF89D" box="[830,1094,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">Fissuroma aggregatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEBFF9DF836F9461EB6F89D" box="[1141,1451,1771,1797]" class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Astrosphaeriella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aggregata">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DF836F9461EB6F89D" box="[1141,1451,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">Astrosphaeriella aggregata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
≡ 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEBFF9DFCE2F8A21AD0F8B1" box="[161,461,1807,1833]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Niessliaceae" genus="Melanopsamma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aggregate">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DFCE2F8A21AD0F8B1" box="[161,461,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">Melanopsamma aggregate</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) was represented by more than 
<specimenCount id="9D2AF4CFFFEBFF9DFF02F8A218FDF8B1" box="[833,992,1807,1833]" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
, two of which have available molecular data (
<collectionCode id="ED3DA783FFEBFF9DFC85F89E1BF1F8D5" box="[198,236,1843,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">KT</collectionCode>
984 = 
<collectionCode id="ED3DA783FFEBFF9DFD7FF89E1A95F8D5" box="[316,392,1843,1869]" country="Japan" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15135" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15135" name="Hirosaki University" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" type="Herbarium">HHUF</collectionCode>
28233, KT 767 = 
<collectionCode id="ED3DA783FFEBFF9DFE1AF89E19B8F8D5" box="[601,677,1843,1869]" country="Japan" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15135" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15135" name="Hirosaki University" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" type="Herbarium">HHUF</collectionCode>
28232) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD42B7FFEBFF9DFF49F89E1F09F8D6" author="Tanaka, K. &amp; Harada, Y." box="[778,1044,1843,1870]" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" pagination="114 - 118" refId="ref5730" refString="Tanaka, K. &amp; Harada, Y. (2005) Bambusicolous fungi in Japan (4): A new combination, Astrosphaeriella aggregata. Mycoscience 46 (2): 114 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10267 - 004 - 0223 - 7" type="journal article" year="2005">Tanaka &amp; Harada 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD42B7FFEBFF9DF863F89E1FEEF8D5" author="Tanaka, K. &amp; Hirayama, K. &amp; Yonezawa, H. &amp; Hatakeyama, S. &amp; Harada, Y. &amp; Shirouzu, T. &amp; Hosoya, T." box="[1056,1267,1843,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" pagination="175 - 209" refId="ref5784" refString="Tanaka, K., Hirayama, K., Yonezawa, H., Hatakeyama, S., Harada, Y., Sano 1, T., Shirouzu, T. &amp; Hosoya, T. (2009) Molecular taxonomy of bambusicolous fungi: Tetraplosphaeriaceae, a new pleosporalean family with Tetraploa-like anamorphs. Studies in Mycology 64: 175 - 209. https: // doi. org / 10.3114 / sim. 2009.64.10" type="journal article" year="2009">
Tanaka 
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DF83BF8991FADF8D5" box="[1144,1200,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD42B7FFEBFF9DF8BCF89E1EBAF8D5" author="Liu, J. K. &amp; Phookamsak, R. &amp; Jones, E. B. G. &amp; Zhang, Y. &amp; Ko-Ko, T. W. &amp; Hu, H. L. &amp; Boonmee, S. &amp; Doilom, M. &amp; Chukeatirote, E. &amp; Bahkali, A. H. B. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Hyde, K. D." box="[1279,1447,1843,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" pagination="135 - 154" refId="ref5209" refString="Liu, J. K., Phookamsak, R., Jones, E. B. G., Zhang, Y., Ko-Ko, T. W., Hu, H. L., Boonmee, S., Doilom, M., Chukeatirote, E., Bahkali, A. H. B., Wang, Y. &amp; Hyde, K. D. (2011) Astrosphaeriella is polyphyletic, with species in Fissuroma gen. nov., and Neoastrosphaeriella gen. nov .. Fungal Diversity 51 (1): 135 - 154. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13225 - 011 - 0142 - 9" type="journal article" year="2011">
Liu 
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DF96EF8991E7BF8D5" box="[1325,1382,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD42B7FFEBFF9DFCCBF8FA1ABCF8EA" author="Phookamsak, R. &amp; Norphanphoun, C. &amp; Tanaka, K. &amp; Dai, D. Q. &amp; Luo, Z. L. &amp; Liu, J. K. &amp; Su, H. Y. &amp; Bhat, D. J. &amp; Bahkali, A. H. &amp; Mortimer, P. E. &amp; Xu, J. C. &amp; Hyde KD" box="[136,417,1879,1906]" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" pagination="143 - 197" refId="ref5418" refString="Phookamsak, R., Norphanphoun, C., Tanaka, K., Dai, D. Q., Luo, Z. L., Liu, J. K., Su, H. Y., Bhat, D. J., Bahkali, A. H., Mortimer, P. E., Xu, J. C. &amp; Hyde KD. (2015) Towards a natural classification of Astrosphaeriella - like species; introducing Astrosphaeriellaceae and Pseudoastrosphaeriellaceae fam. nov. and Astrosphaeriellopsis, gen. nov .. Fungal Diversity 74 (1): 143 - 197. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13225 - 015 - 0352 - 7" type="journal article" year="2015">
Phookamsak 
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DFD63F8F51A46F8E9" box="[288,347,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
). In this study, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEBFF9DFE11F8F519EBF8E9" box="[594,758,1880,1905]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aggregatum">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DFE11F8F519EBF8E9" box="[594,758,1880,1905]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">F. aggregatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode id="ED3DA783FFEBFF9DFF44F8FA1830F8E9" box="[775,813,1879,1905]" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">KT</collectionCode>
767) formed an independent lineage within 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEBFF9DF96DF8F51EB8F8E9" box="[1326,1445,1880,1905]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DF96DF8F51EB8F8E9" box="[1326,1445,1880,1905]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">Fissuroma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEBFF9DFC92F8D11A68F80D" box="[209,373,1916,1941]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aggregatum">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DFC92F8D11A68F80D" box="[209,373,1916,1941]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">F. aggregatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode id="ED3DA783FFEBFF9DFDCBF8D61AB3F80D" box="[392,430,1915,1941]" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">KT</collectionCode>
984) formed a sister branch with 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEBFF9DFF03F8D118EDF80D" authorityName="Y. Feng, S. N. Zhang &amp; Z. Y. Liu" authorityYear="2022" box="[832,1008,1915,1941]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bambucicola">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DFF03F8D118EDF80D" box="[832,1008,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">F. bambucicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<collectionCode id="ED3DA783FFEBFF9DFFBCF8D61F0FF80D" box="[1023,1042,1915,1941]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
comparison of the 936 nucleotides across the 
<collectionCode id="ED3DA783FFEBFF9DFD43F8321A2FF821" box="[256,306,1951,1977]" country="Madagascar" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:12774" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:12774" name="Centre National de la Recherche Appliquée au Developement Rural" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" type="Herbarium">TEF</collectionCode>
gene region of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEBFF9DFDA5F80D198EF821" authorityName="Y. Feng, S. N. Zhang &amp; Z. Y. Liu" authorityYear="2022" box="[486,659,1951,1977]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bambucicola">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DFDA5F80D198EF821" box="[486,659,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">F. bambucicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEBFF9DFE8FF80D1873F821" box="[716,878,1952,1977]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aggregatum">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DFE8FF80D1873F821" box="[716,878,1952,1977]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">F. aggregatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode id="ED3DA783FFEBFF9DFF3DF83218B9F821" box="[894,932,1951,1977]" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">KT</collectionCode>
984) showed 36 bp (900/936 bp) differences. Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEBFF9DFD0DF8691947F845" authorityName="Y. Feng, S. N. Zhang &amp; Z. Y. Liu" authorityYear="2022" box="[334,602,1987,2013]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bambucicola">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DFD0DF8691947F845" box="[334,602,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">Fissuroma bambucicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEBFF9DFFD2F8691F2DF845" box="[913,1072,1988,2013]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aggregatum">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DFFD2F8691F2DF845" box="[913,1072,1988,2013]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">F. aggregatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the three species in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEBFF9DF976F8691EB1F845" box="[1333,1452,1988,2013]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DF976F8691EB1F845" box="[1333,1452,1988,2013]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">Fissuroma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for which no molecular data are available [
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEBFF9DFE22F8451EBAF799" authority="(J. Frohl., K. D. Hyde &amp; Aptroot) Phookamsak &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityName="Phookamsak &amp; K. D. Hyde" baseAuthorityName="J. Frohl., K. D. Hyde &amp; Aptroot" box="[609,1447,2023,2049]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="fissuristoma">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DFE22F8451819F799" box="[609,772,2023,2049]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">F. fissuristoma</emphasis>
(J. Fröhl., K.D. Hyde &amp; Aptroot) Phookamsak &amp; K.D. Hyde
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEBFF9DFCCBF7A11967F7BD" authority="M. Niranjan &amp; V. V. Sarma" authorityName="M. Niranjan &amp; V. V. Sarma" box="[136,634,2059,2085]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="kavachabeejae">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DFCCBF7A11A54F7BD" box="[136,329,2059,2085]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">F. kavachabeejae</emphasis>
M. Niranjan &amp; V.V. Sarma
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEBFF9DFEF7F7A11F88F7BD" authority="M. Niranjan &amp; V. V. Sarma" authorityName="M. Niranjan &amp; V. V. Sarma" box="[692,1173,2058,2085]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="microsporum">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEBFF9DFEF7F7A1187EF7BD" box="[692,867,2060,2085]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="68">F. microsporum</emphasis>
M. Niranjan &amp; V.V. Sarma
</taxonomicName>
] (
<tableCitation id="C6AE0AFDFFEBFF9DF8EAF7A61E07F7BD" box="[1193,1306,2059,2085]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="6.[136,229,158,184]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="TABLE 2. The morphological comparison of Fissuroma bambucicola and several Fissuroma species discussed in this study." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF536FCEFFE9FF9FFCCBFF331BD6FF44" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" tableUuid="DF536FCEFFE9FF9FFCCBFF331BD6FF44">TABLE 2</tableCitation>
.), because of its larger asci and ascospores. In addition, the two ends of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEAFF9CFF59FF3218DAFF20" authorityName="Y. Feng, S. N. Zhang &amp; Z. Y. Liu" authorityYear="2022" box="[794,967,158,184]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="5" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bambucicola">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEAFF9CFF59FF3218DAFF20" box="[794,967,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="69">F. bambucicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
‘s mucilaginous sheath do not protrude, so the distinct morphology of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEAFF9CFDFAFF6E1978FF44" authorityName="Y. Feng, S. N. Zhang &amp; Z. Y. Liu" authorityYear="2022" box="[441,613,194,220]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="5" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bambucicola">
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEAFF9CFDFAFF6E1978FF44" box="[441,613,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="69">F. bambucicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provides strong evidence to be a new species in 
<emphasis id="B958E354FFEAFF9CF8C4FF6E1E18FF44" box="[1159,1285,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="69">
<taxonomicName id="4C2C44C5FFEAFF9CF8C4FF6E1E1CFF44" box="[1159,1281,195,220]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Aigialaceae" genus="Fissuroma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="5" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Fissuroma</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
